			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I bought Advanced Pet Discipline (rank 1 only, natch). Turns out this is an /on /off command, however. That is, when I tell pet to:
<br />
 /kill %t; /focus
<br />

<br />
, the pet responds with "Focusing On Target, Master" IF there is no prior target, now dead and possibly even looted and poofed. IF pet has had a target already /focused, the next mob I send it on causes pet to respond with "No longer focusing on Target"... so I spam the attack hotkey but wth is the point in that?
<br />

<br />
It really has the tiniest impact on play, from usage.
<br />
My advise, skip this next-to-useless AA.
<br />

<br />
and Merry Xmas.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
