			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">ok, its a toggle command, you type /pet focus to toggle it on, so in your case, you press your hotkey, which first send pet, then toggles the focus on, then you press it next time, pet attacks, and focus is toggled off, since you just put it in again
<br />

<br />
you need to /pet focus, toggle it on, then use a normal pet attack, that makes him always focus, it doesnt work like /pet hold where you have to stick it in a macro with /pet back off for it to work how you want it
<br />

<br />
pretty much you just made a mistake in how you made your hotkey, you dont have to toggle it every time, which in doing so resulted in it toggling on and off every fight</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
