			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">No, do not insert it. If you do, it will cause it to toggle /focus ON with the first kill, /focus OFF for second kill, etc.... Just make a fresh hotkey somewhere with ONLY /pet focus. Click this when you summon pet (and I guess after zoning, and maybe after un-suspending just check pets response to be sure it is ON.)
<br />

<br />
Hotkey;
<br />
/pet focus
<br />

<br />
another hotkey;
<br />
/assist Meatshield
<br />
/point (I add a delay for lag so I get assist, not Meatshield, as target)
<br />
/pet attack
<br />
/say Rip %p's heart out Mr Crowley! (optional Roleplay spam)
<br />

<br />
yet another ( <span style="font-weight: bold">I WANT MY IMPROVED PET WINDOW!!</span>;
<br />
/pet hold
<br />
/pet back off
<br />
/say Get the hell off of %t NOW! (Spam is healthy)
<br />

<br />
Graal Macabre</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
