				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yeah, it's a big pita.  Say for instance just for the sake that I'm in the VT stage (yea yea, hitting eles soon, stop laughing <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="Razz" border="0" />)  Say a mob AE nukes and I miss it due to battle spam perhaps, and the fact that many times the AE doesn't hit me myself, so I don't notice it.  My pet is now on that casting mob.  At the particular point in the raid I'm thinking of, we have 7 or so mobs in camp probably.  My pet's on the wrong mob.. so are quite a few others probably.  So mob gets to gating point and nobodys noticing.  Oops, you just let a mob gate.  Now you're in deep shit.  I'm not too too high in the game, I'd be a betting man and say this applies to other places as well, just for raids sake.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
It's a pita to say pet hold.. pet back off... pet kill.  With focus you just say "Pet kill" and it's a done deal.  Never have to wonder if you waited long enough so that your pet's back off took effect and you can instantly switch.  IMO it's a very nice AA.  If you don't like it, don't get it.  Everyone else be will just be uber without you <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="Twisted Evil" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />...and then there were mages...
